HEADWORD: Orometer
<hw>O*rom"e*ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>'o`ros</grk> mountain + <ets>-meter</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Meteor.)</fld> <def>An aneroid barometer having a second scale
that gives the approximate elevation above sea level of the place where
the observation is made.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

